    <subsubsection xml:id="_04-other-notations_attributes">
      <title>Attributes</title>
      <p>In our presentation of crow's foot logical models above, we used text styling (boldface and underlining) to indicate primary keys.  We used italics to indicate foreign keys.  Many drawing and modeling tools similarly use text styling to indicate keys, although not necessarily the styling we used.  Tools may also or instead use background or foreground colors to indicate keys and other properties of columns.</p>
      <p>Many tools will also (or instead) indicate primary and foreign key columns with text indicators, usually <q>PK</q> and <q>FK</q>.  Some will highlight primary keys by separating them from the other columns:</p>
      <image source="PART2_DATA_MODELING/04-other-notations/entity_alternative.svg" width="50%" alt="The entity employee with the primary key attribute labeled with &quot;PK&quot; and with the foreign key attributes labeled with &quot;FK&quot;"/>
      <p>&#x274F;</p>
      <p> </p>
    </subsubsection>
  </subsection>
</section>
